text: Prosopocera bicolor is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae. It was described by Westwood in 1845, originally under the genus Lamia. It is known from Ghana and Cameroon.BioLib.cz - Prosopocera bicolor. Retrieved on 8 September 2014. ==References== Category:Prosopocerini Category:Beetles described in 1845
